<TITLE> 23 JMB militants, including Bangla Bhai's wife, charged </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Mymensingh, Oct 18 (bdnews24.com)  The court of Mymensingh Fourth Additional Sessions judge Mainul Haque Thursday framed charges against 23 members of Islamist militant outfit Jama'atul Mujahidin Bangladesh. The accused, including executed JMB commander Bangla Bhai's wife Fahima, regional commander Salahuddin alias Salehin and member Asaduzzaman Ponir were present in the court. Bangla Bhai's wife Fahima was accused in seven cases including one in connection with the serial bomb blasts in Mymensingh. They are accused in seven cases for simultaneously bombing 11 spots in Mymensingh town including in front of the Mymensingh deputy commissioner's office, district bar association building, Mymensingh Press Club, Pat Gudam bridge crossing, Charpara crossing, Bangladesh Agriculture University, and Ananda Mohan Government College premises. They have also been charged with patronising militants and obstructing government work. Others accused in the cases are Masud, Kausar, Amanullah, Mohibullah, Mahmudul, Ibrahim, Mahmudul Hasan, Ibrahim, Jamaluddin, Sakhawat Hossain, Jamanur Qari, Nizamuddin, Masudur Rahman, Abul Hashem, Tofazzal Hossain, Yasin, Mir Hossain, Kamaruzzaman, Omar Faruk and Mostafizur Rahman. Earlier on Wednesday night Fahima, Salehin and Asaduzzman were brought to Mymensingh jail from Dhaka Central Jail. RAB-9 members arrested Fahima along with her baby son at a house on RK Mission Road in Mymensingh town early in the morning on March 6, 2006. Later, following her confession, Siddiqul Islam alias Bangla Bhai and one of his body guards were arrested from the house of Chan Miah in Rampur village, Muktagachcha upazila. Death sentences against six top militants including JMB supremo Shaikh Abdur Rahman and Bangla Bhai were carried out on March 29, following the verdict in the Jhalakathi judges murder case. Bangla Bhai and Abdul Awal were hanged in Mymensingh Central Jail. Mymensingh zone police CID submitted eight charge sheets in four cases against three militants including Salehin on charges of bomb attacks on four cinema halls in Mymensingh town. Salehin has been sentenced to death by hanging in the verdicts of two murder cases in Jamalpur district. bdnews24.c
